    "prompt_template": "Security-Audit Task: {input}\n\nContext:\n- Security auditing: Identify vulnerabilities, enforce policies, ensure compliance\n- SAST: Static code analysis (Semgrep, CodeQL, SonarQube, ESLint security)\n- Dependency scanning: Snyk, Trivy, npm audit, OWASP Dependency-Check\n- Secret detection: Gitleaks, truffleHog, GitGuardian\n- Container security: Dockerfile review, Hadolint, Kubernetes security\n- IaC security: Terraform (tfsec), Checkov, cloud security reviews\n- DAST: OWASP ZAP, penetration testing\n- Compliance: OWASP Top 10, PCI DSS, HIPAA, SOC 2, GDPR"
  },

  "documentation": "This meta-agent template provides intelligent routing for security auditing tasks across the entire DevSecOps lifecycle. It covers static application security testing (SAST) with tools like Semgrep, CodeQL, SonarQube, and ESLint security plugins. It handles dependency scanning using Snyk, Trivy, npm audit, and OWASP Dependency-Check. Secret detection is supported via Gitleaks, truffleHog, and GitGuardian. Container security reviews include Dockerfile analysis, Hadolint, and Kubernetes security assessments. Infrastructure as Code security covers Terraform with tfsec and Checkov, plus cloud security for AWS, Azure, and GCP. Dynamic application security testing (DAST) uses OWASP ZAP. Compliance auditing supports OWASP Top 10, PCI DSS, HIPAA, SOC 2, and GDPR. Additional features include security code reviews, threat modeling, fuzz testing, supply chain security (SBOM, Sigstore), authentication/authorization reviews, input validation, cryptography reviews, security monitoring, and incident response planning.",
  "examples": [
    "Run a Semgrep scan and configure rules for SQL injection detection",
    "Set up Snyk for dependency scanning in CI/CD pipeline",
    "Configure Gitleaks to detect secrets and API keys",
    "Review Dockerfile for security best practices and vulnerabilities",
